1.  System requirements
The user must satisfy the following conditions to correctly install the software:
* The user must have enough storage space on their computer to download the program
* The user must be able to access and use the command line to start the program
* The user must have RHEL8 64-bit Linux


2.  Setup and Configuration
Download the package from the main directory of this website, or access it from the UCI's servers (for grading purposes only).  Using the command line, go into the installed folder.

For the binary package Chess_Alpha.tar.gz, run the executable program on the command line as follows:
% gtar xvzf Chess_V1.0.tar.gz (extract contents into current directory)
% evince chess/doc/chess.pdf (for reading documentation, if desired)
% chess/bin/chess (run executable file)

For Chess_Alpha_src.tar.gz:
* Extract the Source Package
  * gtar xvzf Chess_Alpha_src.tar.gz
* Build the Software
  * cd chess
  * make
* Run the Executable
  * cd ./bin
  * ./chess
* Remove compiled object files
  * cd ..
  * make clean


3.  Uninstalling
Through the command line, the user can uninstall the program by calling make clean (see above), 
then going one directory above the installed directory and calling rmdir -rf ChessDirectoryName, 
with ChessDirectoryName being the name of the directory that was downloaded by the user 
(the user may have decided to rename the directory, so be sure to check its current name).
